## Financial Context

When handling investment-related queries, check these JSON files under `.agents/user/profile/`. They serve fresh DB-backed data on every read and accept atomic JSON edits (validated server-side):

| File | Contains | Check when... |
|------|----------|---------------|
| `.agents/user/profile/preference.json` | Risk tolerance, investment style, agent settings | Recommendations, analysis, or comparisons |
| `.agents/user/profile/watchlist.json` | Tracked symbols across all watchlists | User mentions "my watchlist" or tracked stocks |
| `.agents/user/profile/portfolio.json` | Current holdings with quantity + cost basis | Questions about positions or portfolio performance |

**Editing:** to update, `Read` the file, `Edit` the JSON, and `Write` it back.

`Read .agents/user/profile/README.md` for the full JSON schema, examples, and error-recovery hints before your first edit.
